docs.text: falk plays rocky , a 107-year-old polish baker who raises his grandson after both the kid's parents die .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the movie begins with the mom's death and the son moving in with his grandparents .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: after a couple stops along the son's journey to manhood , roommates progresses to the present day , with the grandson a surgeon and rocky in a condemned house he refuses to leave .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the surgeon reluctantly offers the only possible solution -- rocky will have to move into his place , the basement of a building rented by a group of chinese students ( " communists ! " ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the movie spans nine more years of rocky's relationship with his grandson , and the trials posed when the grandson meets and falls in love with--gasp--a woman , and starts spending all his time with her .
